## 6. State & Data Flow

### 6.1 End-to-End Flow Through This Module

```
1. Desktop creates experiment:
   POST /experiments { balls }
   → DB: INSERT experiment + balls
   → Response: { experimentId }

2. Phone joins signaling room:
   WS: join { roomId=experimentId, clientId, role="phone" }
   → SignalingHub: room created, "peer-joined" sent to desktop

3. SDP/ICE exchange (relay only):
   Phone WS offer → SignalingHub → Desktop WS
   Desktop WS answer → SignalingHub → Phone WS
   ICE candidates both directions

4. [Recording happens on phone — no Node involvement]

5. Phone uploads video:
   POST /upload/{experimentId}/0  multipart video
   → multer disk write: /experiments/{id}/raw/cam0.webm
   → DB: camera.upload_status = "UPLOADED"
   → WS broadcast: "upload-received"
   → Async: ffmpeg spawned

6. ffmpeg runs:
   → PNG sequence written to /experiments/{id}/frames/cam0/
   → DB: extraction_status = "COMPLETE", frame_count = N
   → WS broadcast: "extraction-complete"
   → Event emitted to JobQueue

7. Desktop submits tracking job:
   POST /jobs { experimentId, type:"tracking", seeds:[...] }
   → DB: INSERT job (status="QUEUED")
   → tryDispatch() → sends gRPC TrackBalls request

8. gRPC streaming:
   For each TrackingStatus message from Python:
   → WS broadcast: "job-progress" { frame, progress, points }

9. gRPC stream ends:
   → DB: job.status = "COMPLETE"
   → WS broadcast: "job-complete"

10. Desktop submits physics job:
    POST /jobs { experimentId, type:"physics" }
    → gRPC ComputePhysics (unary)
    → DB: job.result_json = PhysicsResult JSON
    → WS broadcast: "job-complete" { results }
```

### 6.2 Intermediate Representations

| Stage            | Representation                             | Location                              |
| ---------------- | ------------------------------------------ | ------------------------------------- |
| Pre-upload       | Binary video in phone memory               | Phone (external)                      |
| Uploaded video   | `.webm`/`.mp4` binary                      | `/experiments/{id}/raw/`              |
| Extracted frames | Lossless PNG files                         | `/experiments/{id}/frames/cam{N}/`    |
| DB state         | SQLite rows                                | `/experiments/experiments.db`         |
| Job status       | WS JSON messages                           | In-flight (not persisted)             |
| Physics result   | JSON string in DB + `results/*.json` files | Written by Python, referenced by Node |

### 6.3 What is Retained vs Discarded

| Data                  | Retained?                           | Notes                                     |
| --------------------- | ----------------------------------- | ----------------------------------------- |
| Raw video             | Yes, indefinitely                   | Required for re-extraction or debugging   |
| PNG frames            | Yes                                 | Required by Python on every re-run        |
| ffmpeg stderr         | DB: last 2000 chars on failure only | Not stored on success                     |
| WS signaling messages | No                                  | Pure relay; not logged                    |
| gRPC stream messages  | No (forwarded to WS only)           | Full result stored as `result_json` in DB |
| DB records            | Yes                                 | Permanent until manual deletion           |

